# Core Project Guardrails

## Absolute Priority

This website is SEO-first, performance-first, and Astro-first.

Priority order:

1. SEO and indexability
2. Minimal initial JavaScript
3. Useful HTML without JavaScript execution
4. Fast mobile performance
5. Lightweight, modern, consistent UI
6. Forms visible before wallet connection
7. Wallet/Reown/Solana SDK lazy-loaded only after user action
8. dxra-core-api builds transactions
9. Frontend only signs non-custodial transactions with the user wallet

If a feature makes public pages heavier, less indexable, or more client-side, reject it unless explicitly approved.

When there is a conflict between more features and a lighter, more indexable page, choose the lighter and more indexable page.

---

## Stack

Use:

- Astro
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Static Astro components for public layout
- React islands only for truly interactive tool forms, uploads, previews, transaction/action flows, or controls that cannot be safely handled with minimal Astro/TypeScript
- React Hook Form + Zod only inside form islands
- dxra-core-api wrappers for transaction building
- Non-custodial wallet signing on the frontend after user action

Do not use:

- Full React SPA for public pages
- React for Header, Sidebar, or Footer
- Ant Design
- MUI
- Chakra
- HeroUI/NextUI
- Flowbite React
- Rewind UI package
- Framer Motion
- global animation libraries
- global wallet providers
- global Reown initialization
- global Solana SDK imports
- legacy Next.js API routes copied into Astro
- one huge legacy `solanaHandlers.js` file

shadcn/ui may be used only inside React islands for complex form UI when explicitly requested.

Do not use shadcn/ui for:

- Header
- Sidebar
- Footer
- static SEO sections
- static cards
- static modals/sheets
- public layout shell

---

## Change Scope Rule

When asked to modify one area, modify only that area.

Examples:

- If asked to polish Header, do not redesign Sidebar/Footer.
- If asked to polish modals, do not refactor wallet logic.
- If asked to fix styling, do not add dependencies.
- If asked to improve UI, do not increase JavaScript.
- If asked to refactor, do not redesign visuals unless requested.
- If asked to work on UI/UX, do not change SEO copy/routes unless explicitly requested.
- If asked to fix build/dependencies, do not redesign UI.

Do not create new components, scripts, or architecture unless explicitly requested.

Exception:
A small shared Astro component may be created only when all of these are true:

- the same pattern already appears in 3+ places
- it reduces total repeated markup
- it stays within the requested area
- it adds no JavaScript
- it does not change behavior
- it does not introduce a new dependency

Never use “consistency” as a reason for broad refactoring outside the requested scope.

Not allowed:

- creating new architecture layers without explicit need
- broad refactors outside the requested scope
- replacing static Astro UI with React
- adding dependencies for simple UI patterns
- changing unrelated files because they are nearby
- changing routes or SEO structure while doing a visual task

---

## No Bulk Cleanup Rule

Do not perform broad cleanup, formatting, renaming, token migration, route migration, or component extraction unless explicitly requested.

Do not “fix” unrelated code while working on a specific task.

Do not change many files to improve style consistency unless the task explicitly asks for a design-system refactor.

Prefer the smallest safe change that solves the requested problem.

---

## Astro Layout Rule

These must remain Astro/static:

- `src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro`
- `src/components/layout/Header.astro`
- `src/components/layout/Sidebar.astro`
- `src/components/layout/Footer.astro`
- SEO content sections
- FAQs
- breadcrumbs
- related links
- static cards
- warnings and safety notes
- footer/internal link sections
- trust/safety sections

Do not hydrate static navigation.

Header/sidebar/footer must not import:

- React UI libraries
- wallet libraries
- Reown
- Solana SDK
- Raydium SDK
- Meteora SDK
- Orca SDK
- Jito logic
- transaction logic

Public pages must render meaningful HTML without JavaScript execution.

---

## Initial JavaScript Rule

Initial JS must stay as close to zero as possible.

Allowed tiny JS only for:

- theme persistence
- mobile sidebar open/close
- desktop sidebar collapsed state
- header settings/modal open/close only when already implemented
- wallet button click trigger
- small accessibility helpers for menus/dialogs
- tiny preference persistence such as network/priority fee

Do not add global layout scripts.

Do not bundle in the initial public layout:

- `@reown/appkit`
- `@reown/appkit-adapter-solana`
- `@solana/web3.js`
- `@solana/spl-token`
- wallet-adapter packages
- Raydium SDK
- Meteora SDK
- Orca SDK
- Jito logic
- heavy charting libraries
- CSV parsing libraries
- transaction builders

Any heavy library must be dynamically imported only after explicit user action.

---

## Wallet / Reown Rule

Header may show a wallet button, but wallet code must load only after explicit user click.

Allowed:

- Static Astro wallet button
- Tiny click handler
- Dynamic import after click: `import("../../lib/wallet/reown-client")`
- Showing cached connected address if implemented without loading the wallet SDK
- Updating wallet button text after user interaction

Only this file may import Reown packages:

```txt
src/lib/wallet/reown-client.ts
```

Never:

- initialize Reown on page load
- initialize Reown in Astro frontmatter
- initialize Reown in layout/header/sidebar/footer
- use global wallet provider
- load Reown via `client:load`, `client:idle`, or global React island unless explicitly approved
- require wallet connection before the form is visible
- hide the whole form behind a wallet connect button

Forms must remain visible and mostly fillable before wallet connection.

Wallet is required only for the final transaction action.

Good button states:

- `Connect Wallet to Continue`
- `Review Transaction`
- `Create Token`
- `Sign Transaction`
- `Submitting...`
- `Transaction Sent`

Bad UX:

- `Connect Wallet` required to see the form
- loading wallet libraries when the page loads
- global wallet provider in layout
- wallet SDK inside public static content

---

## dxra-core-api / Transaction Rule

Transaction construction must be separated from UI and wallet signing.

Use this flow:

1. Static Astro page renders SEO and explanatory content.
2. React form island collects and validates input.
3. Client sends validated payload to dxra-core-api wrapper.
4. dxra-core-api returns raw/unsigned transaction data.
5. Frontend lazy-loads wallet only when user chooses to sign.
6. User signs non-custodially in wallet.
7. Signed transaction is submitted/polled through the approved transaction layer.

Do not:

- build transactions directly inside header/sidebar/footer
- import Solana SDK into public static layout
- put private RPC URLs or API secrets in frontend
- expose server secrets
- copy legacy Next API routes into Astro
- copy one huge `solanaHandlers.js` into the new project

Preferred structure:

```txt
src/lib/dxra-api/
src/lib/transactions/
src/lib/validation/
src/lib/tool-actions/
src/islands/forms/
```

---

## Security Rule

Never expose secrets in frontend code.

Do not expose:

- private RPC URLs
- Helius API keys
- Pinata JWT
- Jito private config
- server secrets
- internal routing config
- private API keys
- signing keys

Allowed public env values:

- `PUBLIC_DXRA_CORE_API_URL`
- `PUBLIC_SITE_URL`
- `PUBLIC_DEFAULT_NETWORK`
- `PUBLIC_REOWN_PROJECT_ID`

All public env values must be safe to expose in browser source.

