## Design Direction

The UI must feel:

- serious
- modern
- clean
- technical
- trustworthy
- calm
- lightweight
- user-friendly
- readable
- compact without feeling cramped

Avoid:

- crypto casino style
- excessive neon
- huge gradients
- glassmorphism everywhere
- oversized controls
- tiny unreadable gray text
- decorative clutter
- dashboard-heavy UI
- random one-off styles
- too many competing accent colors
- visually loud hover states
- page sections that look unrelated to each other

Use:

- subtle borders
- soft surfaces
- clear typography
- compact controls
- readable spacing
- simple active states
- one main blue/cyan accent
- violet only for premium/PRO states
- semantic warning/danger/success colors
- consistent radius and control heights

Wallet button should usually be the strongest global action in the header.

Secondary controls such as Network, Fees, Theme, and PRO must not overpower the primary wallet/action button.

