## Shared UI System Rule

Repeated UI patterns should use shared Astro components instead of one-off Tailwind blocks when reuse is clear.

Use shared components for repeated:

- buttons
- cards
- badges
- alerts
- inputs
- textareas
- selects/radio groups
- dialog shells
- section headers
- tool cards
- FAQ blocks
- warning boxes
- empty states
- CTA sections

Preferred component examples:

```txt
src/components/ui/Button.astro
src/components/ui/Card.astro
src/components/ui/Input.astro
src/components/ui/Alert.astro
src/components/ui/Badge.astro
src/components/ui/DialogShell.astro
src/components/ui/SectionHeader.astro
src/components/ui/ToolCard.astro
src/components/ui/FaqBlock.astro
```

Do not create all preferred UI components upfront.

Create shared components only when needed by the current task.

Do not replace simple working markup with abstractions unless duplication is already clear and the change reduces complexity.

A shared component should make the project easier to maintain, not just move Tailwind classes into another file.

Shared components must:

- use semantic tokens from `tokens.css`
- support light and dark mode
- stay compact and mobile-friendly
- avoid JavaScript unless required
- expose simple variants only
- keep accessible focus states

Allowed variants should stay limited.

Button variants:

- `primary`
- `secondary`
- `ghost`
- `danger`
- `warning`
- `success`
- `pro`

Badge variants:

- `neutral`
- `brand`
- `success`
- `warning`
- `danger`
- `pro`

Alert variants:

- `info`
- `success`
- `warning`
- `danger`

Do not add a new visual variant unless it is reused in at least 3 places or explicitly requested.

