## Visual Token Rule

Use `src/styles/tokens.css` as the source of truth for:

- colors
- surfaces
- borders
- radius
- shadows
- control heights
- layout sizes
- focus rings
- modal dimensions
- sidebar/header dimensions
- semantic status colors
- premium/PRO colors

Use the existing token naming scheme already present in the project.

Do not rename existing tokens globally unless explicitly requested.

If the project currently uses tokens such as `--background`, `--foreground`, `--card`, `--border`, or `--ring`, keep them stable.

New semantic tokens may be added only when they are reused in 3+ places and do not conflict with existing tokens.

Do not create random hardcoded colors or radii inside components.

Allowed:

- Tailwind spacing and responsive utilities from the approved scale
- small layout utilities like `gap-2`, `px-4`, `text-sm`
- one-off values only when they solve a specific responsive issue and are not reusable
- protocol/logo colors only when they are part of the logo itself

Do not create a new token unless it will be reused in at least 3 places.

Scripts should control state with attributes/classes, not inject hardcoded color styles.

Preferred pattern:

```html
<button data-selected="false">Mainnet</button>
```

```css
[data-selected="true"] {
  background: var(--color-nav-active);
  color: var(--color-nav-active-text);
  border-color: var(--color-nav-active-border);
}
```

---

## Layout Sizing

Use shared layout tokens.

Current header height:

```css
--header-height: 3.5rem;
```

Do not hardcode:

- `top-16`
- `h-16`
- `4rem`
- `64px`

for layout positioning unless `--header-height` is also updated intentionally.

Sidebar and mobile backdrop must use:

```css
top: var(--header-height);
height: calc(100vh - var(--header-height));
```

Desktop sidebar collapsed width must use:

```css
--sidebar-collapsed-width
```

Keep layout dimensions centralized.

Do not create conflicting sidebar/header sizes in individual components.

