## Light/Dark Contrast Rule

Every UI change must be checked in both light and dark mode.

Required:

- body text must be clearly readable
- muted text must not be used for important instructions
- borders must be visible but subtle
- active states must be obvious
- disabled states must remain readable
- cards must be distinguishable from page background
- dialogs must have stronger surface separation than normal cards
- header/sidebar/footer must feel related but not visually merged
- hover/focus states must be visible in both themes

Avoid:

- dark text below slate-500 on important light-mode content
- gray text below slate-400 on important dark-mode content
- dark surfaces that blend into the page background
- active states that rely only on color without border/background change
- low-contrast disabled controls
- bright neon accents on large surfaces

