## React Island Rule

React islands are allowed only for interactive pieces.

Allowed React islands:

- forms
- wallet/action flows
- uploads
- transaction preview
- CSV parsing
- small dynamic tool controls when Astro + tiny TypeScript is insufficient

Not allowed as React islands:

- Header
- Sidebar
- Footer
- SEO content
- FAQs
- static tool descriptions
- static cards
- breadcrumbs
- related links
- blog/guides
- trust/safety pages

Header, Sidebar, and Footer controls must prefer Astro + minimal TypeScript.

Do not create React islands inside Header, Sidebar, or Footer unless explicitly approved.

A wallet button in the header must not be a React island by default.

React islands must not import wallet/Solana SDKs at top level unless they are already behind a user action and intentionally lazy-loaded.

Prefer dynamic imports for heavy logic inside the event handler.

---

## Shared Token Selector / Heavy Component Rule

Shared components used across many forms must not make every page heavy.

For heavy shared controls such as token selectors:

- keep the visible shell lightweight
- load search/indexing/data logic only after focus/open/user action
- debounce network requests
- avoid importing Solana SDK for public key validation
- avoid global stores
- avoid loading token lists on initial page load unless required
- split heavy parsing/search code into dynamic imports
- keep SEO content outside the island

Do not let a shared form component become a hidden site-wide bundle tax.

