## Header Rule

Header must remain:

- Astro-first
- compact
- mostly static
- visually calm
- responsive
- no global wallet/Reown
- no Solana SDK
- no heavy client logic

Desktop header may include:

- brand
- network selector
- fee control
- PRO entry
- theme toggle
- wallet button

But visual hierarchy must remain clear:

1. wallet/action button = primary
2. network and fee = secondary utility
3. PRO = special but not louder than wallet
4. theme = utility icon

Header controls must not wrap at desktop/tablet breakpoints.

At smaller desktop widths, shorten labels before increasing height.

Mobile header must include:

- menu button
- compact brand
- wallet/action button
- settings only if space allows

No horizontal scroll.

---

## Sidebar Rule

Sidebar must remain:

- Astro/static
- readable
- compact
- category-based
- usable expanded and collapsed
- consistent in light/dark mode

Collapsed sidebar:

- must not create awkward floating/overlapping submenus unless explicitly designed and tested
- should expand first when user interacts with a category if that is the simpler UX
- must not cause horizontal scroll
- must remain keyboard usable where possible

Sidebar item labels must be consistent and professionally capitalized.

Avoid repetitive labels like:

- `Pump.fun Zone`
- `Meteora Zone`
- `Orca Zone`

Prefer cleaner labels:

- `Pump.fun`
- `PumpSwap`
- `Meteora`
- `Orca`
- `LaunchLab`

Do not remove useful categories without explicit approval.

---

## Footer Rule

Footer must remain:

- static Astro HTML
- no JavaScript
- no React
- no wallet imports
- clear and useful
- not oversized
- visually balanced

Footer should include:

- brand summary
- useful tool links
- category links
- trust/safety or non-custodial note
- legal/support links if needed

Do not add decorative clutter.

Do not add newsletter/forms unless explicitly requested.

---

## Modal / Dialog Rule

Dialogs and mobile sheets must use a consistent shell style.

Shared expectations:

- same panel radius
- same surface token
- same border token
- same close button style
- same header/title spacing
- same subtitle/helper text scale
- same mobile sheet behavior
- Escape closes when JS exists
- outside click closes when JS exists
- focus styles visible

Use shared classes or shared components when dialog patterns repeat and the component stays simple/static.

Do not use a heavy dialog library for simple header/settings dialogs.

Do not make every modal look like a separate product.

---

## Animation Rule

No motion animations.

Do not use:

- transform animation
- scale hover
- slide animation
- fade animation
- animated gradient
- page transition
- global animation library

Allowed only if needed:

- `transition-colors`
- max 150ms
- hover/focus border/background color only

If strict no-animation is requested, remove transitions entirely.

Never add Framer Motion globally.

---

## Accessibility

Interactive controls must be real buttons or links.

Required:

- `aria-label` for icon-only buttons
- `aria-expanded` for menus
- `aria-controls` for controlled panels
- visible focus styles
- readable contrast in light and dark mode
- keyboard closable dialogs/menus where JS exists
- Escape closes modals/menus where JS exists
- meaningful links use `<a>`
- actions use `<button>`
- decorative icons use `aria-hidden="true"`

Do not use clickable divs.

Do not rely on color alone for important active/error states.

---

## Icons

Use:

- `@lucide/astro` for static Astro UI icons
- local inline SVGs for protocol logos

Do not use:

- `react-icons`
- icon fonts
- animated icons
- global icon imports
- random icon libraries

Icon sizes:

- sidebar icons: 16px to 18px
- card icons: 20px
- hero/tool icons: 24px to 32px max

Decorative icons need `aria-hidden="true"`.

Meaningful icon-only buttons need accessible labels.

Protocol logos should remain lightweight and local.

